                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\"><placeName>Pto Cabello</placeName>, <date>June 15,\n                1854</date>.</p>\n            <p>\n                <addressee>Isaac Leeser Esq</addressee>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">\n                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">Dear sir,</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I had this pleasure per Barque Paez <date>1st</date><lb/> inst. and\n                avail of this opportunity to beg of you the<lb/> kindness to procure for me the\n                Portrait of the Love<add>?</add><lb/> Giver in a plain ebony frame, but if it cost\n                too high<lb/> I would prefer any other of dark wood, also to send<lb/> me a volume\n                of “Select Sentences,” one volume poems<lb/> by <persName>Mrs Hyneman</persName>—a\n                Jewish Calendar for fifty years,<lb/> one vol. Of <persName>Miss\n                    Peixotto's</persName> book of Bible questions</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Trusting that you will excuse me for troubling<lb/> you so often,\n                and in hopes that you may put it in<lb/> my way to reciprocate your kindness.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(4)\">I remain, Dear sir,</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(5)\">Yours most faithfully</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(6)\">\n                <persName role=\"author\">A Myerston</persName>\n            </p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3g737q3n/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
